<br>
What if the people he named wanted to hide their player's gender, for example?  What if he said &quot;Fred, player of Didi&quot;?  That gives away more than just a first name, suddenly there would be dozens of people going 'ack, she's a guy!'.  Or, what if one of them is hiding their identity from someone (e.g. an ex)?  I've been stalked around electronic forums before, by an ex who knew I hung out on a certain BBS but didn't know which user I was.  If anybody had posted my real name, he'd've started harassing me nonstop.<br>
<br>
Sure, these are examples that probably don't apply in the current case.  But there's many potential violations of privacy whenever real names are named, I don't think you can just dismiss it saying 'no harm done'.  You don't know what harm was done.<br>
<br>
I'd be quite happy for everybody who names real names to be banned.  No sympathy here.  <br>
<br>
